caption: Amazing, delightful atmosphere! Romantic and an authentic Italian setting!  Food was so wonderful(shrimp divolo and chicken piccata)and the Staff, cannot say enough about them! Our favorite, Juan Buruca, amazing in many ways!  We wanted a Lyft, but could not grab one, he offered us a ride to our hotel.  So thoughtful.   He’s one in a million!  This is a must stop for authentic Italian food.   Awesome wine list as well.   Truly a great experience.

The service is amazing from seating to departure.  The staff was very accommodating of dietary concerns and everything was cooked to perfection. The food was as tasty as being in Tuscany.  The takeout delivery has been so busy at this restaurant and was very busy the evening we visited. It caused our dessert to arrive a little later than expected. They comped our dessert.  Such customer service.  That's why I keep coming back.
Wonderful food, service, and atmosphere. Perfect for dates, family dinners, or just an evening out with some friends and good food.

Don’t waste your money on this place. We ordered it through DoorDash and it was awful. To begin with it was way over priced for for a small portion. We ordered garlic bread and it was burnt and small pieces. Also we order penne all arrabbiata and it was too spicy to the point it was not edible.
The Veal Marsala was excellent! I would recommend them to anyone!!
Delicious
The food is delicious and the ambiance is nothing short of amazing. I always feel like I'm in a classy quintessential DC spot. Definitely go for an escape for yourself or for a date to impress.

Did a call in order..I was craving steak with Alfredo noodles though it was not on the menu they made it for me. It was $40. However I was told by the waiter that because I asked too many questions I would have to pay over the phone. No lie! I marched inside and demanded the manager...he explained that waiters have to pay for orders not picked up. I understood, I apologized to the waiter and tipped him generously...he forgave me with 2 huge glasses of wine on the house LOL  manager was super nice we had great convo. Meal was 8/10. Steak medallions were weirdly soft texture I’ve never had before almost like veal but nonetheless it was good.
Amazing food, great service, will be back.
Good food

I love the food here but I have a problem with the Tiramisu. I don’t know if this is just how this restaurant makes it but there’s almost no ladyfingers and it’s basically just a soup of the cream. I have to go on a hunt to find the actual ladyfingers. There’s also almost no cocoa powder on top. But otherwise I like the restaurant a lot, I’m just kind of sad about the Tiramisu, it’s my favorite desert and having to eat it like this is a little defeating.

Delicious food at a reasonable price. I ordered a watermelon salad with arugula, feta cheese, and balsamic vinegar with fresh mint leaves on top followed by agnolotti pasta stuffed with spinach and ricotta cheese in a pink sauce. Both were excellent. The salad was refreshing, and the pasta was very light.

I ordered via Door Dash and something happened where they didn't get the order and they were kind enough to take my word for it and send me my order and sort out the payment with Door Dash directly. Superb customer service!

Came from out of state and wanted Italian so we ordered from here. We ordered take out so my review could have been much different if we would have eaten there but a toddler makes that difficult. The box of lasagna was smashed and leaking all over everything. My husband's pasta was decent but my meat lasagna was really greasy which then gave me a bellyache afterwards. We later ate our dessert which was very good.
Best food ever! Great customer service even through COVID! Ask them or tell them what ur craving and they are well informed on the menu to hit ur craving!!!! ADVISE anyone near the area to stop by

You can't just put plain cream and bacon together with spaghetti and call it carbonara! It is literally not carbonara, at all. Where is the egg, parmesan, and garlic? Such crucial ingredients for the dish. How can you call it carbonara when it does not contain the ingredients that make it unique?
Beautiful service
Best place ever! The servers are super nice and the food is delicious!
Delicious food, great service, pleasant atmosphere.
Excellent food and service. This is a great place to go for a relaxing and fun Italian meal.

(Translated by Google) Exquisite Italian food, very attentive staff and if you speak with the owner you will know a success story in the development of your business  (Original) Exquisita comida italiana, personal muy atento y si hablas con el propietario conocerás una historia de éxito en el desarrollo de su negocio
The best Italian in The District! The food is always perfect.
The food was so-so. Definitely not worth the price.

Trattoria Alberto has decent Italian food, but it's nothing to write home about. I've never had anything super interesting or complex, flavor wise. The staff are friendly though and I'm willing to go when others want to because it's a pleasant experience.  They do have excellent chocolate gelato (it's the children's bear dessert).

I found this jewel of the city by luck.   I was looking for an Italian restaurant and this Trattoria Alberto popped up.   I was so pleasantly surprised by how delicious the food and dessert was.   The service was excellent and everyone was super nice.  I could not ask for a more awesome meal than this one.  This is a must-visit restaurant if you're in DC.

Although we've lived on the Hill for years this was the first time we've visited this place.The food was excellent. The calamari appetizer was tasteful and excellently prepared. I had a steak topped with crab sauce and the steak was melt in your mouth tender.My only complaint was I wish there was more of the crab sauce topping but this in no way detracted from the meal. I dont remember the name of the wine but it was an very tasty pairing ,red mildly dry,that complemented the meal. Generous portions of my wife's meal had her smiling  during the entire evening. We were there with friends who are regulars and I was thoroughly impressed with the attention and service and friendliness of the staff. We most certainly will be going back and hope to fo so on a frequent basis.
The food was delicious. The waitress was bit oblivious
Just ok. Had the penne arabiatta. Small portions but high price. Dining room is cozy looking.
Great Food
If you love Italian food you will love this place I've never had a bad meal here
Good freindly service, comfortable environment, tasty food. Went early just as they were opening before a world series game, food came out fast, will try this place again during next years season.

The food and service were both exceptional. A date night for my wife and I. Extra bonus points for a romantic restaurant that you can also carry a conversation on in. So many places are so noisy but the ambiance at Trattoris was perfect for our evening out.
Everything about this place is perfect. The service is exceptional. Bottles of wine were half priced! The food was phenomenal. I imagine that this is what they serve in heaven.

Awesome authentic Italian without breaking the bank. If you're looking for a more casual experience in the DC area this is a great spot. They have outdoor seating for those that want to take in Barrack's Row, as well as a bar area if you're looking to grab a drink. I had their salmon with white wine sauce over spaghetti and it was delicious!

The homemade pastas and specialty dishes have never disappointed! Service is excellent with superb attention to detail. The cucumber mint martini is exceptional! A very friendly place with delicious choices.
My absolute favorite Italian restaurant on Capitol Hill!

I had such a great time and the food was wonderful! Very comfortable welcoming atmosphere and a wide variety of options. The pasta is homemade too!

Trattoria Alberto is a wonderful spot to dine if you expect attentive and friendly service. Unlike some traditional Italian spots, their pasta dishes are often paired with a hearty meat option together, so you don’t have to order a pasta and meat dish separately along with your pasta. The outdoor seating area is great for people watching in the warmer months, and they’ve got 1/2 priced bottles of wine on special on Fridays. Also a great place to book for larger parties for a birthday or special event because they’ve got two larger dining room areas that you can reserve with either a full or fixed menu.
Not only food was really good, the customer went beyond amazing!. Staff was very helpful with my 1 year old twin boys.
My goto Italian place for an intimate meal. Impeccable service, really good food, white tablecloths, and a very apropos atmosphere.

Neighborhood Italian, nondescript from the outside, delicious on the inside. Every night has at least three specials: fish, pasta, and veal. Understated and earnest. The staff is well trained and attentive, the prices reasonable by DC restaurant standards. Kids welcome but price points make Alberto's more an adult meal place. No background music, but by the middle of the dinner hour (and into a bottle of wine) voices get louder (but never so loud you can't continue a conversation). Long history on Capitol Hill, current ownership has only enhanced and invigorated. (Legislators sometimes spotted there, either for working dinner or night out with spouse).

Went for a friends birthday dinner and they lied and said they had a private room wrong they put us on the ground floor dining room; and gave some of are tables away and the FOOD was not that well and the chicken Parmesan tasted like McDonald's chicken nuggets with tomato sauce on top; The ultimate atmosphere is NOT MINORITY FRIENDLY; will not be coming back or recommending to anyone.

Great

Had dinner here earlier tonight and really nothing about it was good. The bread they bring out the beginning of dinner was stale, the $29 seafood special was really terrible with rubbery calamari and squid and slim lobster shells with no meat.  My girlfriend had the fusilli primavera which came with broccoli, carrots and zuchinni as the vegetables and noodles that came out of a box.  You could easily make this at home for 1/4 the cost.  We didn't order drinks, but they're really over-priced at $8.5 dollars for house wine.  I really don't understand how other people rated this place so highly.  I'd say this is my least favorite restaurant experience in D.C.

I was introduced to Trattoria Alberto by my cousin Frankie who raved about it for months. The quaint neighborhood eatery exceeded my expectations and I’ve never had anything less than a wonderful experience there.  The food is always excellent and beautifully presented, the prices reasonable; the wait staff attentive and entertaining.  Living near Dulles, I don’t get to Trattoria Alberto as often as I would like, but always book a reservation for special celebrations or intimate dinners. And when friends or family come to town, it is one of the restaurants I always recommend.  Fogeddaboudit!

I totally enjoyed my dining experience at Trattoria Alberto!  And here's why:  1. Atmosphere - I decided to go here on a whim and it seemed very tight at first...until I went to the restroom and saw all of the nooks and crannies!  4 floors of seating!  Very intimate, very nostalgic, very cool and it reminded you of being at your grandma's house with the family over on a Sunday afternoon.  2. Service - I had no problem with the service at all.  As a matter of fact, the service was pretty awesome.  There was a cute blonde girl who waited on us and she wasn't pushy, she was very attentive and knew exactly when to check on us.  Everyone else on staff was very nice.  3 Food - Starting out with the calamari fritti, I ended up getting a chicken and pasta dish and my wife a scampi dish which she loved.  We both finished our plates and ordered desert.  The canoli was simply to die for!  4. Drinks - I ordered Amaretto Sours the entire night because I like Disarrono...and the were absolutely yummy!  I will NOT divulge how many I had...ahem!  =]  5. Price - for the price, it was an excellent night.  Expect to spend around $80-$100 bucks for both you and the lady and a nice bottle of wine will considerably jump the total but it's well worth it if you like quiet, intimate and cozy settings.  I loved this place!  You know, as I walked down the half-spiral stairway, I walked back out on to DC streets and felt as if I left a different world.  Such a familiarity, such a cozy, warm environment, I would definitely recommend this place again and again!

I stopped in for lunch one day and had the chicken picata, it was terrible.  It was like chicken cutlets in fake half warmed butter sauce with a grit that felt like i was chewing on sand.  I was scared to eat it but i was so hungry.  They brought me the wrong drink and various other service mistakes.  I had about 3 waiters waiting on me and none of them took care of me.  I would avoid this restaurant.  I heard the current owner bought the place from the original owners and worked for Fragers Hardware before owning the restaurant (and they are not Italian).  I know many local old timers swear by it but i think they are just holding on to the way it once was.
